      • createRestaurant

        @RequestMapping(value="/owner/restaurants",
                method=POST)
public org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity<java.lang.Object> createRestaurant​(@RequestBody
                                                                                  com.example.demo.model.Restaurant restaurant,
                                                                                  @CurrentUser
                                                                                  com.example.demo.model.MyUserPrincipal principal)
        This method creates a restaurant and assigns it to the currently logged in user. If the user already has a restaurant, then the restaurant is updated. If data fields from the input are empty, then those fields are not changed. Then the restaurant is saved to the database and restaurant repository.
        Parameters:
        restaurant - A restaurant object as a JSON
        principal - A user object with username and password that holds the current logged in user.
        Returns:
        Http Status Code ResponseEntity
